C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20Trump%20purposely%20trying%20to%20trigger%20a%20recession%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%20holding%20up%20a%20board%20showing%20reciprocal%20tariffs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ee7c8cb8b41a9673fc85ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETrump's%20new%20tariffs%20may%20disrupt%20economic%20recovery%20and%20increase%20consumer%20prices%20%E2%80%94%20by%20design.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20not%20some%20sort%20of%20fringe%20conspiracy%20theory%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ben%20McMillan%20of%20IDX%20Advisors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESlower%20growth%20could%20mean%20lower%20interest%20rates%20and%20a%20more%20manageable%20national%20debt%20load.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-today-trump-tariffs-trade-war-sp500-dow-nasdaq-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20trade%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20many%20scratching%20their%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPost-pandemic%20inflation%20seemed%20to%20be%20mostly%20under%20control%2C%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20appeared%20to%20have%20the%20economic%20soft-landing%20in%20the%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Trump's%20broad-based%20tariffs%20announced%20on%20Wednesday%20threaten%20to%20upend%20progress%20on%20both%20fronts.%20By%20imposing%20import%20taxes%20on%20foreign%20goods%2C%20consumer%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20rise.%20The%20pullback%20in%20spending%20that%20theoretically%20should%20result%20from%20inflation%20could%20then%20cause%20an%20economic%20contraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20is%20Trump%20doing%20this%3F%20Trump%20reasons%20that%20his%20policies%20will%20bring%20manufacturing%20jobs%20back%20to%20the%20US%20over%20the%20long%20haul%20after%20decades%20of%20free%20trade%20sent%20them%20overseas%20for%20cheaper%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20another%20line%20of%20thought%20might%20be%20behind%20Trump's%20trade%20war%3A%20by%20causing%20economic%20chaos%2C%20he%20could%20be%20trying%20to%20bring%20down%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20the%20US%20to%20essentially%20refinance%20its%20debt%20at%20a%20much%20cheaper%20cost%20and%20prevent%20debt%20levels%20from%20spiraling%20to%20even%20further%20extremes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20interest%20rates%20soared%20thanks%20to%20the%202022%20inflationary%20environment%2C%20interest%20payments%20alone%20on%20US%20debt%20are%20projected%20to%20cost%20almost%20%241%20trillion%20in%202025%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Peter%20G.%20Peterson%20Foundation.%20That's%20around%2013.5%25%20of%20the%20government's%20budget%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20the%20economy%20were%20to%20go%20into%20recession%2C%20the%20Fed%20would%20presumably%20cut%20interest%20rates%20significantly%2C%20and%20investors%20would%20flock%20to%20risk-free%2010-year%20Treasury%20notes%2C%20pushing%20down%20their%20yields%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20interest%20the%20government%20pays%20on%20the%20borrowed%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYields%20on%2010-year%20Treasurys%20have%20fallen%20significantly%20since%20Trump's%20inauguration%2C%20dropping%20from%204.6%25%20to%204.05%25%2C%20where%20they%20sit%20as%20of%20Thursday%20midday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20not%20some%20sort%20of%20fringe%20conspiracy%20theory%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ben%20McMillan%2C%20CIO%20at%20IDX%20Advisors.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20coin%20flip%20as%20to%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20the%20intention%2C%20but%20there%20have%20been%20some%20data%20points%20that%20suggest%20it's%20a%20non-trivial%20possibility%20in%20my%20mind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20those%20data%20points%2C%20according%20to%20McMillan%2C%20include%3A%20Trump%20saying%20at%20Davos%20this%20year%20that%20he'll%20demand%20interest%20rates%20fall%3B%20his%20apparent%20willingness%20to%20tackle%20the%20debt%20problem%20in%20unconventional%20ways%2C%20like%20offering%20%245%20million%20gold%20card%20residency%20permits%3B%20and%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%20saying%20there's%20no%20%26quot%3BTrump%20put%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20administration%20would%20cave%20on%20its%20policies%20to%20placate%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20everyone%20thinks%20this%20explanation%20is%20as%20plausible.%20When%20asked%20in%20a%20March%20interview%20with%20BI%20if%20Trump%20was%20intentionally%20trying%20to%20lower%20interest%20rates%20by%20bringing%20on%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20Desmond%20Lachman%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20conservative-leaning%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%20and%20a%20former%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20official%2C%20said%20it%20was%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20you're%20being%20too%20generous%2C%26quot%3B%20Lachman%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20they're%20clueless%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20they%20know%20what%20they're%20doing%20because%20basically%20what%20he%20does%20is%20on%20Monday%20he%20puts%20the%20tariff%20on%2C%20on%20Tuesday%20he%20takes%20it%20off%2C%20on%20Wednesday%20he%20puts%20it%20back%20on%20and%20makes%20an%20exemption%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20making%20policy%20on%20the%20fly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20follow-up%20email%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Lachman%20reiterated%20this%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20action%20that%20Trump%20took%20yesterday%20on%20tariffs%20confirms%20that%20he%20has%20no%20clue%20what%20he%20is%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Lachman%20said%20about%20Trump's%20so-called%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%20blanket%20tariffs.%20%26quot%3BThis%20move%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20plunge%20both%20the%20US%20and%20world%20economy%20into%20a%20recession.%20It%20is%20already%20causing%20a%20world%20stock%20market%20rout.%20I%20do%20not%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20Trump's%20intention%20to%20crash%20the%20economy%20as%20that%20will%20have%20a%20very%20high%20political%20cost%20for%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20Trump's%20true%20intentions%2C%20recession%20risks%20are%20rising%20by%20investors'%20and%20Wall%20Street's%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20sunk%20as%20much%20as%204.3%25%20since%20market%20close%20on%20Wednesday%20while%2010-year%20Treasurys%20gained%20as%20investors%20fled%20risk%20assets%20in%20favor%20of%20safety.%20And%20some%20banks%20have%20increased%20their%20recession%20odds%20since%20the%20start%20of%20Trump's%20trade%20war%3A%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20for%20example%2C%20recently%20bumped%20its%20recession%20odds%20to%2035%25%20from%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-trump-crashing-the-economy-on-purpose-trade-war-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743705010000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eec25369253ccddf9b2a8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-trump-crashing-the-economy-on-purpose-trade-war-tariffs-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20the%20trade%20war%20Trump's%20strategy%20to%20bring%20down%20interest%20rates%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22wedwards%40businessinsider.com%20(William%20Edwards)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A398%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-trump-crashing-the-economy-on-purpose-trade-war-tariffs-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Anupam%20Kher%20spoke%20about%20falling%20in%20love%20with%20Kirron%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743704592000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%