22.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EActress%20Hansika%20Motwani%20and%20her%20mother%2C%20Jyoti%20Motwani%2C%20have%20petitioned%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20to%20quash%20a%20case%20of%20cruelty%20registered%20against%20them%20under%20Section%20498A%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS).%20The%20complaint%20was%20filed%20by%20Hansika%E2%80%99s%20sister-in-law%2C%20Muskan%20James.%20Muskan%20James%2C%20a%20television%20actress%2C%20married%20Prashant%20Motwani%2C%20Hansika's%20brother%2C%20in%20December%202020.%20However%2C%20their%20marriage%20ended%20in%20separation%20two%20years%20later%2C%20in%20December%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftelugu%2Fmovies%2Fnews%2Fhansika-motwani-mother-jyoti-move-bombay-high-court-to-quash-cruelty-case-filed-by-sister-in-law%2Farticleshow%2F119953622.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PM%2C%20Bangladesh's%20Yunus%20Sit%20Next%20To%20Each%20Other%20At%20Summit%20Dinner%20In%20Bangkok%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Muhammad%20Yunus%2C%20the%20Chief%20Advisor%20of%20the%20interim%20government%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20sat%20side%20by%20side%20during%20the%20official%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20the%20Thai%20Prime%20Minister%20Paetongtarn%20Shinawatra%20for%20the%20visiting%20Heads%20of%20States%20and%20Head%20of%20Governments%20on%20Thursday%20attending%20the%20BIMSTEC%20summit%20in%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20X%20handle%20of%20Chief%20Advisor%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20Bangladesh%20posted%20screen%20grabs%20of%20both%20leaders%20sitting%20side%20by%20side%20at%20the%20dinner%20table%20as%20the%20Thai%20PM%20welcomed%20the%20BIMSTEC%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20media%20in%20Bangladesh%20quoted%20Chief%20Advisor's%20Deputy%20Press%20Secretary%20Abul%20Kalam%20Azad%20as%20saying%20that%20both%20leaders%20%26quot%3Bmet%20each%20other%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20official%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interim%20government%20has%20been%20keen%20on%20holding%20first-ever%20bilateral%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20BIMSTEC%20summit%20in%20Bangkok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BIMSTEC%20chairmanship%20will%20be%20officially%20handed%20over%20to%20Bangladesh%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Advisor's%20High%20Representative%20on%20Rohingya%20and%20Priority%20Issues%20Khalilur%20Rahman%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20the%20leaders%20of%20BIMSTEC%20member%20states%20will%20discuss%20their%20future%20works%20with%20Yunus%20and%20there%20is%20a%20scope%20to%20hold%20the%20meeting%20between%20Yunus%20and%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20requested%20India%20to%20hold%20this%20talk%20(between%20the%20leaders%20of%20two%20countries)...there%20is%20enough%20possibility%20of%20holding%20this%20meeting%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahman%20said%2C%20addressing%20a%20press%20briefing%20in%20Bangladesh%20ahead%20of%20the%20BIMSTEC%20Summit%20in%20Thailand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20PM%20Modi%20had%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20Yunus%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20the%20National%20Day%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20highlighting%20the%20significance%20of%20mutual%20sensitivity%20while%20referring%20to%20the%20Bangladesh%20Liberation%20War%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bshared%20history%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20remain%20committed%20to%20advancing%20this%20partnership%2C%20driven%20by%20our%20common%20aspirations%20for%20peace%2C%20stability%2C%20and%20prosperity%2C%20and%20based%20on%20mutual%20sensitivity%20to%20each%20other's%20interests%20and%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20PM%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20been%20worried%20about%20the%20deteriorating%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh%20under%20the%20current%20interim%20government.%20The%20Yunis%20regime%20has%20been%20criticised%20severely%20for%20acquitting%20extremist%20elements%20and%20exonerating%20many%20Islamists%20since%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Awami%20League%20government%20led%20by%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20in%20August%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20support%20a%20stable%2C%20peaceful%2C%20inclusive%20and%20progressive%20Bangladesh%20in%20which%20all%20issues%20are%20resolved%20through%20democratic%20means%20and%20by%20holding%20inclusive%20and%20participatory%20elections.%20We%20remain%20concerned%20about%20the%20deteriorating%20law%20and%20order%20situation%2C%20which%20has%20further%20been%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20release%20of%20violent%20extremists%20who%20were%20sentenced%20for%20serious%20crimes%2C%26quot%3B%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20has%20stated%20on%20several%20occasions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Bangladesh%20slid%20into%20abyss%20following%20the%20fall%20of%20Awami%20League%20government%2C%20the%20Yunus-led%20regime%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20giving%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20the%20Islamist%20forces%20in%20the%20country%20and%20also%20relaxing%20comprehensively%20the%20policy%20of%20mandatory%20security%20clearance%20required%20for%20Pakistani%20citizens%20seeking%20visas%2C%20thus%20facilitating%20easy%20return%20of%20many%20notorious%20terror%20suspects%20who%20had%20earlier%20fled%20to%20the%20safe%20havens%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20end%20still%20in%20sight%20to%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20particularly%20on%20members%20belonging%20to%20the%20Hindu%20and%20Ahmadiyya%20communities%2C%20the%20MEA%20has%20repeatedly%20highlighted%20the%20serious%20issue%20and%20the%20interim%20government's%20botched%20up%20investigations%20that%20have%20so%20far%20been%20just%20an%20eyewash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20repeatedly%20underlined%20that%20it%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20interim%20government%20of%20Bangladesh%20to%20protect%20Hindus%20and%20other%20minorities%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20properties%20and%20religious%20institutions.%20As%20seen%20so%20far%2C%20only%201254%20out%20of%202374%20reported%20incidents%20between%20August%205%2C%202024%2C%20and%20February%2016%2C%202025%2C%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20the%20police.%20Further%2C%2098%20per%20cent%20of%20these%201254%20incidents%20were%20deemed%20political%20in%20nature.%20We%20expect%20Bangladesh%20to%20thoroughly%20investigate%20and%20bring%20all%20perpetrators%20of%20killings%2C%20arson%2C%20and%20violence%20to%20justice%20without%20making%20such%20distinctions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson%20has%20mentioned%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20(EAM)%20S.%20Jaishankar%2C%20during%20his%20meeting%20with%20Bangladesh%20Foreign%20Affairs%20Advisor%20Touhid%20Hossain%20in%20Muscat%2C%20conveyed%20that%20it%20is%20important%20that%20Bangladesh%20should%20not%20normalise%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743703740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fqatg0a0c_modi-yunus-ians_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpm-modi-bangladeshs-yunus-attend-bimstec-dinner-in-bangkok-8080490%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Muhammad%20Yunus%2C%20the%20Chief%20Advisor%20of%20the%20interim%20government%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20sat%20side%20by%20side%20during%20the%20official%20dinner%20hosted%20by%20the%20Thai%20Prime%20Minister%20Paetongtarn%20Shinawatra.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpm-modi-bangladeshs-yunus-attend-bimstec-dinner-in-bangkok-8080490%22%2C%