3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUSAID's%20human%20resources%20staff%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20have%20been%20on%20paid%20administrative%20leave%20and%20face%20termination%2C%20have%20been%20brought%20back%20to%20the%20office%20to%20send%20out%20accurate%20notices%2C%20said%20the%20US%20official%20and%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20letter%20was%20completely%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20USAID%20worker%20told%20Reuters%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20correct%20was%20my%20name.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20inaccurate%20termination%20notices%20have%20upended%20the%20lives%20of%20USAID%20workers%20since%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Musk%20began%20in%20February%20to%20dismember%20America's%20main%20conduit%20of%20foreign%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20first%20round%20set%20April%2021%20as%20the%20final%20employment%20day%20for%20most%20personnel%20and%20May%2030%20for%20those%20tapped%20to%20help%20shutter%20the%20agency.%20Those%20dates%20were%20reset%20to%20July%201%20or%20September%202%20in%20the%20notices%20sent%20to%20some%203%2C500%20USAID%20workers%20last%20Friday%2C%20two%20sources%20and%20workers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20errors%20included%20inaccurate%20start%20dates%2C%20lengths%20of%20service%20and%20salaries%2C%20according%20to%20the%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%2C%20the%20US%20official%2C%20two%20former%20senior%20USAID%20officials%2C%20a%20congressional%20aide%20and%20four%20workers%20who%20received%20notices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnless%20fixed%2C%20those%20mistakes%20could%20result%20in%20reduced%20or%20canceled%20pensions%20or%20inaccurate%20severance%20pay%2C%20the%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20the%20sources%20pointed%20to%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management's%20retirement%20website%20that%20says%20federal%20workers'%20annual%20pension%20annuity%20is%20based%20on%20their%20le